<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,433,817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
The so-called Tahiti “sand-bug” is probably the common intertidal 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hombron &amp; Jacquinot, 1846)" authorityName="Hombron &amp; Jacquinot" authorityYear="1846" baseAuthorityName="Hombron &amp; Jacquinot" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippidae" genus="Hippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[942,1149,434,457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Hippa marmorata</emphasis>
(Hombron &amp; Jacquinot, 
<number box="[151,211,469,493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1846.0">1846</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the senior synonym of the better known 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dana" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[686,811,469,493]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippidae" genus="Hippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis box="[686,811,469,493]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">H. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dana" box="[827,973,469,493]" firstAuthor="Dana" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref10288" refString="Dana, J. D. (1852 b) Crustacea, Part I. United States Exploring Expedition, During the Years 1838, 1839, 1840, 1841, 1842, Under the Command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N., vol. 13 (2), i - viii, 1 - 685; Atlas (1855), 1 - 27, pls. 1 - 96, C. Sherman, Philadelphia. Davie, P. J. F. (2002) Crustacea: Malacostraca: Phyllocarida, Hoplocarida, Eucarida (Part 1). In: Wells, A. &amp; Houston, W. W. K. (Eds.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia, vol. 19.3 A. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, 551 pp." type="book chapter" year="1852" yearSuffix="b">
Dana, 
<number box="[902,959,469,493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1852.0">1852</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1825" box="[996,1105,469,493]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hippidae</taxonomicName>
). However, two other species are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[344,544,505,529]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1787" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[557,879,505,529]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippidae" genus="Hippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adactyla">
<emphasis box="[557,690,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">H. adactyla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius" box="[699,879,505,529]" firstAuthor="Fabricius" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref10621" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1787) Mantissa Insectorum sistens eorum species nuper detectas adiectis Characteribus genericis, Differentiis specificis, Emendationibus, Observationibus. Hafniae, 1, i - xx, 1 - 348." type="journal article" year="1787">
Fabricius, 
<number box="[820,879,505,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1787.0">1787</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1862" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1862" box="[942,1338,505,529]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippidae" genus="Hippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ovalis">
<emphasis box="[942,1046,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">H. ovalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Milne-Edwards" box="[1055,1338,505,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="17 - 19" refId="ref12266" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1862) Faune carcinologique de l'ile de la Reunion. In: Maillard, L. (ed.), Notes sur l'ile de la Reunion, Annexe F, F 1 - F 16, pls. 17 - 19." type="journal article" year="1862">
A. Milne-Edwards, 
<number box="[1282,1338,505,529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Poupin" firstAuthor="Poupin" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="1" refId="ref12738" refString="Poupin, J. (1996) Crustacea Decapoda of French Polynesia (Astacidea, Palinuridea, Anomura, Brachyura). Atoll Research Bulletin, 442, 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1996">
Poupin 
<number box="[151,210,541,565]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1996.2005">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poupin" box="[221,281,541,565]" firstAuthor="Poupin" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" refId="ref12770" refString="Poupin, J. (2005) Systematique et ecologie des crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes de Polynesie francaise. Memoire Presente par Habilitation a Diriger les Recherches Universite de Perpignan, Faculte des Sciences, 115 pp." type="book" year="2005">2005</bibRefCitation>
), and their conspecificity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtiss" authorityYear="1938" box="[629,853,541,565]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnoldorum">
<emphasis box="[629,853,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Cancer arnoldorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be discounted. In any case, a revision of the genus is urgently needed (Boyko &amp; McLaughlin 
<number box="[711,767,577,601]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="2011.0">2011</number>
) and Curtiss’s name should be resolved conclusively then, perhaps with the appropriate designation of a 
<typeStatus box="[673,765,614,638]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">neotype</typeStatus>
. Joseph Poupin (personal communication) commented that he collected an ovigerous female, ostensibly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curtiss" authorityYear="1938" box="[701,927,649,673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arnoldorum">
<emphasis box="[701,927,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Cancer arnoldorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, among the black sand in front of Vaitepiha River near Tautira in Tahiti, with his photograph showing a bluish-purple animal. This agrees well with the colour described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Curtiss" box="[305,533,721,745]" firstAuthor="Curtiss" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref10067" refString="Curtiss, A. (1938) A short zoology of Tahiti in the Society Islands. Guide Printing, Brooklyn, New York, pp. i - xvi, 1 - 193." type="book chapter" year="1938">
Curtiss (
<number box="[403,464,721,745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="1938.0">1938</number>
: 
<number box="[477,523,721,745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" value="167.0">167</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
: “The front part of its body is bluish above, with an almost smooth shell, and whitish underneath”. Like in other parts of the Pacific, these and their allies (the so-called mole crabs) are often harvested for food.
</paragraph>
